com.kaazing.gateway.server.spi.security

Class AuthenticationToken

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kaazing.gateway.server.spi.security.AuthenticationToken

  • public abstract class AuthenticationToken
extends Object
    An authentication token is comprised of (usually) one or more component strings. AuthenticationToken models the collection of components as an integer-indexed and/or as a name-indexed collection that together form the complete "token".

      • getScheme

        public abstract String getScheme()
        Return the authentication scheme (e.g. "Basic", etc) that was used by the client to provide this token to the server. Note that the scheme can be null, i.e. if the token data came from cookies.
        Returns:
        the HTTP authentication scheme, or null is no HTTP authentication scheme was used to provide the token data.
